      "content": "thanks for that, that makes more sense. one thing i was reading about is how blockages can mess everything up. like if something gets inside the tube, it'll give a totally wrong reading. can you explain how a blockage in either the pitot tube or the static port affects the airspeed indicator? like what happens to the needle if the pitot tube gets plugged?",
      "source": "evaluator"
